<section class="bg--white">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
        <h4 class="color--orange title-font-alt text-center">Authors</h4>
        <hr class="center" style="width: 20%;"/>
        <h1 class="color--orange text-center">
          Mazzula &bull; Serrata
        </h1>
      </div>
    </div>
    <br/><br/><br/>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-7">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1">
                <h4 class="type--bold margin-bottom-10">Introduction</h4>
                <h4 class="">
                  Developing culturally relevant human services for racial and ethnic minorities has become a
                  national priority. However, understanding what works, how it works, and why it works within
                  certain cultural-specific communities continues to be severely limited, despite efforts of
                  professional fields to promote multicultural practice. This limitation is only intensified
                  when looking at the subpopulation of boys and men within communities of Color. One way to fill
                  this gap is to utilize a cultural-specific framework to guide the scan of various sources of
                  knowledge (e.g., academic literature and community-led products).
                </h4>
                <hr/>
                <div class="row">
                  <div class="col-md-6">
                    <h5 class="type--bold no-margin">Authors</h5>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Silvia Mazzula, PhD</li>
                      <li>Josephine V. Serrata, Ph.D.</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <hr/>
                <p class="center">
                  <%= link_to fieldscans_download_fs6_url, class: "btn btn--sm btn--block btn--rise-orange" do %>
                    Download Full Report <i class="material-icons">&#xE2C4;</i>
                  <% end %>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-5">
            <%= image_tag("fieldscans/fs6/fs6.png", class: "box-shadow-light")%>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
